{{Infobox language |name=Bauré |nativename= |states=[[Bolivia]] |ethnicity=980 (2006)<ref name=e18/> |speakers=40 |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Maipurean languages|Arawakan]] |fam2=Southern |fam3=Bolivia–Parana |fam4=Moxos |dia1=Joaquiniano |iso3=brg |glotto=baur1254 |glottorefname=Baure-Carmelito-Joaquiniano }}
'''Bauré''' is a nearly extinct [[Arawakan languages|Arawakan]] language spoken by only 40 of the thousand Baure people of the Beni department of northwest of Magdalena, [[Bolivia]]. Some Bible portions have been translated into Baure. Most speakers have been shifting to [[Spanish language|Spanish]].
Baure has an [[active–stative]] syntax.<ref>Aikhenvald, "Arawak", in Dixon & Aikhenvald, eds., ''The Amazonian Languages'', 1999.</ref>
