{{Infobox language |name=Bhujel |nativename=Bujhyal |region=[[Tanahu District]], [[Nepal]] |speakers={{sigfig|21,700|2}} |date=2011 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Chepangic languages|Chepangic]] |iso3=byh |glotto=bujh1238 |glottorefname=Bujhyal }}
'''Bhujel''', also called '''Bujhyal''', is a [[Chepangic languages|Chepangic]] language spoken in central [[Nepal]]. It is a semi-[[tonal language]], employing a complex array of [[affix]]es.
==Geographical distribution== Bhujel is spoken in the following villages of Nepal (''[[Ethnologue]]'').
*[[Tanahun District]], [[Gandaki Zone]]: [[Kulmun]], [[Arthumpka]], [[Andimul]], and [[Baniyatar]] *[[Gorkha District]], [[Gandaki Zone]]: [[Beltar, Nepal|Beltar]] *[[Nawalparasi District]], [[Lumbini Zone]]: [[Dhodeni]] *[[Chitwan District]], [[Narayani Zone]]: [[Chanaute]]
==Dialects== ''[[Ethnologue]]'' lists the following dialects of Bhujel.
*Kulmun *Arthumpka *Andimul *Baniyatar *Beltar *Dhodeni *Chanaute
