{{Infobox language |name=Chepang |nativename=''Chyo-bang'' |region= [[Nepal]] |ethnicity=[[Chepang people|Chepang]] |speakers={{sigfig|48,500|2}} |date=2011 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Chepangic languages|Chepangic]] |iso3=cdm |glotto=chep1245 |glottorefname=Chepang |script= [[Devanagari]] }}
'''Chepang''' is a language spoken by approximately 37,000 people in [[Nepal]]. The people are known as [[Chepang people|Chepang]]. [[Randy LaPolla]] (2003) proposes that Chepang may be part of a larger "[[Rung languages|Rung]]" group.
==Geographical distribution== Chepang is spoken in the following [[districts of Nepal]] (''[[Ethnologue]]'').
*[[Makwanpur District]], [[Narayani Zone]] *[[Chitwan District]], [[Narayani Zone]] *Southern [[Dhading District]], [[Bagmati Zone]] *Southern [[Gorkha District]], [[Gandaki Zone]]
Dialects are Western Chepang and Eastern Chepang.
