{{no footnotes|date=December 2012}}
'''Paio Soares de Taveirós''' or ''Paay Soarez de Taveiroos'' seems to have been a minor [[Galicia, Spain|Galician]] nobleman and [[troubadour]] active during the second and third decades of the 13th century. He was a brother of the troubadour [[Pêro Velho de Taveirós]]. Of his works, six ''[[cantiga de amor|cantigas de amor]]'', three ''[[cantiga de amigo|cantigas de amigo]]'', and two ''[[tenso]]s'' (one with [[Martim Soares]] and one with his brother) survive.

He may have been one of the earliest authors in [[Galician-Portuguese lyric]], and his ''[[Cantiga da Garvaia]]'', a satiric ''cantiga de amor'' (or  ''[[cantiga d'escarnho|cantiga de escárnio]]'') is one of the most famous poems in the corpus.

