[[Tirukkural]] has been translated into [[Rajasthani language|Rajasthani]] only once.
==Background== In 1982, the Kural text was translated into Rajasthani by Kamala Gurg. Titled ''Tirukkural Needhi Sastra,'' this was published in [[Jaipur]]. This remains the sole translation of the Kural text into Rajasthani.<ref name="OOCities_RajPunj">{{cite web | url = http://www.oocities.org/nvkashraf/kur-trans/Ind-Int.htm | title = Thirukkural in Punjabi and Rajasthani | last = | first = | date = | website = OOCities | publisher = | access-date = 23 April 2017 | quote = }}</ref>
